{
  "texts": [
    "Coaches typically employ four main methods to provide feedback to badminton students.",
    "First, the coaches provide verbal feedback to the students to inform them of their performance and whether they have executed the correct stroke.",
    "If a student still has difficulty maintaining the proper posture or executing the correct movement, the coach may demonstrate an example to clarify the appropriate form.",
    "Additionally, some coaches may use video feedback to help students track their progress or observe the correct motion of a skilled player.",
    "However, while video feedback can be effective for some students, it may not always be the most useful tool for everyone."
  ]
}